ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The title of the course is what you'll get out of it.I would definitely recommend to anyone interested in economic and/or fiscal dynamics.
Yes! It is a great class to truly understand how Wall street works and Washington works (or doesn't work) in a philosophical background employing a cultural lens for Main Street.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Greatcourse and I will use the material in my professional experience frequently.

Yes. I now understand much more about Wall street especially and the Hill. When before Wall street seemed like an amorphous polar opposite to my public policy ideals, I now see the incentives, stereotypes, and behaviors that make up Wall Street and the crisis. Likewise, I also now more clearly understand the outward and inward role of Washington.
